restaurant.name: The Pharmacy Burger Parlor & Beer Garden
restaurant.timings: Lunch, Dinner, Late (Sun, Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat)

photo.caption: Stroganoff Burger w/ sweet potato fries

review.review_text: It was very cold dinner night and we were given place near outdoor it was really cold in restaurant and burger was not that great in taste i have tasted better burger then this. The restaurant style.music and environment was great but i felt there was something i really did not feel anything spl about it and yes service also nice...

Gonna get some disagreements after this review but went into this place thinking it was one of the better burgers in Nashville from some people who have been here and was very disappointed. Burger was well done and hard as a rock. Tater tots were about only thing on par. Wouldn’t travel 15 minutes out here ever again for that

DELICIOUS!  I had the Stroganoff Burger with sweet potato fries.  The mushroom bechamel on the burger was so so good.  I also very much enjoyed the homemade buns.  The fries were okay, not crispy, but tasty.
Food was good. Priced very reasonably. Good selection of beer and ciders. The wait was 60+ minutes even after we waited the 60-90 minute range through the no wait app.
Great atmosphere and location, it always seems busy. The menu was good but the drinks were great. The staff were very friendly and helpful. I'll be back again soon!

restaurant.name: Loveless Cafe
restaurant.timings: 7 AM to 9 PM (Mon-Sun)

photo.caption: Country fried steak and fried chicken

review.review_text: The food and atmosphere was fantastic southern. The food is great. The staff is friendly. I had southwest omelette and bisquitte and gravy. All excellent. The price was reasonable no complaints.

Went for lunch 9/9/18 we got fried chicken fried catfish chicken gizzards with turnip greens fried green tomatoes fried okra white beans geeen beans Mac and cheese and fudge pie was all wonderful food and the service was impeccable

When I came here I was expecting a touristy spot, especially since they have a whole Loveless subculture with stores & all sorts of branded stuff nearby. However, I found it honestly good southern food. The meats there were great and the drinks were excellent too. The service was extremely good as well. I got to see why they are such a famous place - there's really nothing you can blame here. They seem to have it figured out

Where to Eat Instead Of Loveless Cafe  feast.media/where-to-eat-instead-of-loveless-cafe Loveless Cafe has been a staple of the Nashville community and what I like to call the world wide community of soul food lovers, or the WWCOFS for short. Many people know this genre of food as soul food, meat and three, southern, or even comfort food. As a native of Nashville, I have been coming to Loveless since before I was born. For a while all the hype was true, Loveless was the best place to go if you want real southern food. However, more than just management changed years ago, and it hasn't been able to restore the former quality that everyone from this town remembers. Now Loveless is busier than they ever have been and the food isn't even half as good.   Now, this next piece of information isn't something to go spreading around to everyone you know visiting or living in Nashville. The reason this place is special is because there aren't herds of people being bussed in to wait 45 minutes in line for cheese grits slathered in a stack of Kraft American singles to the point you feel like you're drinking processed cheese whiz with a sprinkle of grits. You won't feel like you are inside a chain restaurant owned by Opryland. There isn't anyone trying to sell you merchandise while you are cooped up in the waiting area trying to decide whether or not you want to wait any longer for this food.   Where you want to go instead of Loveless is a magical place on Old Hillsboro road right outside of the Nashville city limits that goes by the name Barbara's Home Cooking. If you have been to Loveless and you first arrive at Barbaras, you will be wondering where the line is? Well, I have literally never seen a line there and they have open seating. Once you walk into this home turned restaurant, the lovely women who run the place will greet you with authentic South African accents and the warmest, densest, fluffiest, roll that has ever melted in your mouth. The menu is written on a chalkboard on the wall and almost never changes. The benefit to not having tons of options is that they are able to make everything as fresh as possible.

I went into my meal at Loveless thinking "This must be an overhyped tourist spot". Boy, was I wrong. It's honest and delicious southern comfort food. I went with my family, so we did the family style meal. For our meats, we got fried chicken and pulled pork. Both were great, but the fried chicken was probably the best I've ever had. It's done right. I wouldn't go there for the pulled pork, but it was still better than I expected. For our sides, we got macaroni and cheese, mashed potatoes and gravy, and hash brown casserole. The macaroni and mashed potatoes were superb. However, I didn't find myself drawn to the hashbrown casserole as much. It was great, but not the best I've had.  Overall, I'd give Loveless an A+. The staff is friendly and warm. There's always a long wait, but there's a reason for that- Everyone wants to eat there. It's one of the best food experiences I've had around the Franklin area. 10/10 recommend.

restaurant.name: Hattie B's Hot Chicken
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 10 PM (Mon-Thu),11 AM to 12 Midnight (Fri-Sat),11 AM to 4 PM (Sun)

photo.caption: Great food and there's always a line outside of Hattie B's

review.review_text: Have been to Hattie B’s, Princes and Bolton’s for hot chicken. Hattie B’s was good, but the wait and the crowded restaurant detracted from the experience for this diner.  Princes, in my opinion, is the best.

Found this place when we were traveling. We’d never heard of hot chicken before, and now I feel like Ive wasted the first part of my life.   We stopped in at 2pm in the afternoon and the line was out the door and down the sidewalk. For the size of the line, they got us in pretty quick. It was a tight squeeze in the restaurant. It’s small and was packed but it was worth it. The staff was very friendly and helpful.  We got a half chicken, medium heat, and a kids meal with mild heat. Sides were mac & cheese, coleslaw, and fries.  The chicken was hot, fresh and delicious. White meat in general can be kind of dry sometimes but theirs was not. The medium heat was spicy enough that hubs was happy (he likes things hot) but not so spicy I couldn’t eat it. They brought us ranch dressing to go with our chicken. I was a little sad to see it come out pre packaged. We probably wouldn’t have used much of it anyway except maybe on those awesome fries. The chicken was awesome by itself.  The mac & cheese was nice and creamy, and the pimento wasn’t over powering but you could appreciate it. The fries we awesome. Crispy, with a great seasoning. And the coleslaw was fresh, not soggy. Hubs and I like our slaw sweet but this wasn’t. It was good for regular slaw. The kiddo loved the coleslaw.  It was a winner all the way around. We will definitely make this a go to stop on our travels out east.
Good stuff. Something everyone should try. Nashville is known for their hot chicken. This is one of the places you need to visit. Always a long line so plan ahead.

All I can say is awesome and worth the wait. Got the large dark dam hot and it was dam hot . I loved the sweet heat, sweating and tearing up a little  it was great chicken, banana pudding was good , Collier greens ok red skin potato salad was good as well.

As a Nashville hot chicken enthusiast, I'd never been to Hattie B's until I stopped into the brand new Melrose location tonight. The chicken was great! I don't love all my food super spicy all the time but I like my chicken hot so I went with a small dark meat leg quarter, "hot" level. I thought it was perfect. Mac and cheese was decent but the collard greens were meh, although I'm from the midwest so I've only ever been impressed by southern greens once. Overall I have to recommend the chicken but the sides got a mediocre score.

restaurant.name: Pancake Pantry
restaurant.timings: 6 AM to 3 PM (Mon-Fri),6 AM to 4 PM (Sat-Sun)

review.review_text: Absolutely delicious!  We arrived early on a Tuesday and didn’t have to wait.  Within 20 minutes, there were folks lined up out the door!  I had the Santa Fe with cornmeal pancakes that were scrumptious. My friends delighted in an omelet and waffle and ham and eggs with pecan pancakes.  Everything was made to order and perfect!  Highly recommend!

Food was great. Not the best I’ve had but it’s the best I’ve had in this state so far. But it is definitely second favorite place. I had the banana bread pancakes with bananas on top. The eggs I got with cheese and it looks as if they put real cheese on them. Fantastic. Not everyone does that. It was packed so we ended up sitting with a stranger which we had a choice. We didn’t mind. We were starving after running the Nashville half marathon. But we didn’t wait long and we are definitely going back as I plan to take my parents as well.

Wow wow wow. Craziest pancake menu I have ever seen.  I ordered the heart attack ! Not actually the heart attack but looks like one. Was very good with banana pancakes. Had break fast at 9 and it is 1230 know and I'm still full. Very good.

Located in the cute village-like Belmont/Hilsboro district in Nashville you can't go wrong with pancakes that have been served for years at this mom & pop local gem. Apparently sourcing speciality Tennessee flour helps these little beauties. The sweet potato pancakes are light and fluffy and complimented with cinnamon syrup. The corn and jalapeño are chunky and dense but still tasty. Many options to try, something for everyone - not far (close drive) from the 'I love Nashville' mural, Reese Witherspoon's Draper James boutique, and the Parthenon (yes, Nashville you are the Athens of the South ;) ) worth a visit for a great southern pancake breakfast. Care, queues exist often we've been told.

With great expectations, I went to the Pancake Pantry and was prepared to be impressed.  The first impression was the parking.  It was a grease-fire, at best.  It too almost as long to park as it did to eat.  Luckily, there was not a wait, as it was a weekday.  The service was advertised and very nice and professional.  As for the food, the pancakes were light, fluffy and good, but I have had better at many other places.  The sausage was not good at all and the eggs/toast were average.  The coffee was good and the atmosphere was nice.  They had a nice gift area, but as everything else in Nashville, it was overpriced.  If I could do it again, I would not.

restaurant.name: Fido
restaurant.timings: 7 AM to 11 PM (Mon-Sun)

review.review_text: I first found Fido 4 years ago on the advice of a chef friend who lived in Nashville for a while. Fish tacos to die for. Great coffee. Neighborhood feel. I have returned every year and it does not disappoint. I am headed there at this very moment as my first Nashville stop on my drive from Maine.

My husband and I decided to try Fido for breakfast this morning after seeing all the good reviews. We arrived about 10:45 parked in back and got right in. At Fido you go to the counter to order and they bring out your food. My husband got the chorizo and eggs breakfast($10) which came with tortillas and hash browns as well as sour cream and salsa. I chose the steak and eggs scramble without the onion. My breakfast was $11 and came with hash browns and a piece of toast. We also got a chocolate biscotti and an orange cranberry scone. I waited on our drinks while my husband found us a table. We tried the biscotti while we waited on our meals. The biscotti was excellent and is made in house. Our breakfasts came out surprisingly quick, Both were very good. My eggs had fresh spinach and Gouda cheese and the hash brown were hand cut. Fido is eco friendly and uses paper straws. We were full so we took the scone to go.

The line was long but the service was fast. I had the BBQ Sammy.  If was lacking a sauce. Somewhat dry but the overall texture was pretty good. Came with some chicken soup that had more onions than chicken. With some hot sauce it got a lot better. I would give my first experience there a 3.6 but believe other items could be better.
AMAZING breakfast! It exceeded my expectations! Probably in the top 2 breakfast places I’ve ever been to. Definitely worth stopping, even if there’s a wait!!

I love Fido's and so does my family. My favs-breakfast all day and the Eden salad.  If Eggs Benedict is the Daily Special, I'm all over that. It does have quite the wait sometimes, but the food is delicious.

restaurant.name: Jacks Bar-B-Que
restaurant.timings: 10:30 AM to 9 PM (Mon-Thu), 10:30 AM to 10 PM (Fri-Sat), 11 AM to 7 PM (Sun)

photo.caption: Beef Brisket Plate with Mac-n-Cheese and Green Beans and a side of Cornbread

review.review_text: Best Bar b q in town.  Great Atmosphere awesome.  employees.  Ribs are to die for and the pork too!    Spacious room upstairs for bigger groups.   Lots of bar b q sauce.  And employees are awesome!
Pork shoulder was amazing. Some of the best bbq in the USA. Fun atmosphere too!!!    There is often a line.  Lots of seating indoor and out.  Right by the Ryman on Broadway.  Affordable
This is a great place to eat. There's always a crowd, any time of the day and yet the service was super fast. Clean bathrooms and I saw an employee actually wash his hands.

December 31, 2016 ·							by willoughbyandy ·							in Barbecue, Southeast, Tenneessee														· Leave a comment. Not realizing that there was a free New Year’s Eve concert in downtownNashville, we headed down to Broadway to grab some lunch.  That explained the cordoned off streets and exorbitant parking (at noon).  We found a paid lot next to the Ryman and walked down to Broadway in the drizzle.  We turned the corner past Tootsie’s and as soon as we passed Robert’s Western World, we found ourselves standing at the end of the line waiting to go into Jack’s Bar-B-Que.  Originally opening in 1989 at the corner of Broadway and First Avenue, Jack lost his lease to development by the riverfront (to a spot that became the Hard Rock Cafe) and moved up Broadway to the current location – they’ve since opened two additional locations in town.A line stretching out the door at 1:30 on a Saturday is usually a sign of one of two things – either there is excellent food or they are the only game in town.  I could see other restaurants across the street, so we were hoping for the former.  The good thing about the line is that we weren’t waiting for a table – we were actually in the line for counter service, where you order.   It was  fifty to sixty people deep, but we moved through it and up to the steam table and register in about twenty minutes.  Actually, instead of “we”, I moved up there while my beloved snagged a table for two, by the window.  Actually, it was a table pushed up against the window with half a booth for seating.  It made for cozy dining.

BBQ was decent. Was more of a kitchen with a mess hall dining area as to be expected for fast food. Didn't really have much of an atmosphere. Going downtown Nashville one would expect live music and cheery entertainers. BBQ had decent flavor with little smoke. I had the smoked sausage and it had a good snap to it but not entirely too much smoke. Their mac and cheese was good though. I tried their sweet and smoky sauce which was nice.

restaurant.name: McNamara's Irish Pub & Restaurant
restaurant.timings: Lunch, Dinner (Sun, Tue, Wed, Thu),  (Mon),Lunch, Dinner, Late (Fri-Sat)

review.review_text: Pretty awesome place to eat. Live music and outstanding food. Probably won't eat there again though because this business backed down to their customers and replaced the lamb in their "authentic" Shepherd's Pie with cow.

This is a fun spot for a very Irish night out. They have delicious Irish fare - I would recommend their Scotch eggs. They also have some very lively musicians and a great vibe. Good experience altogether.

First, when you walk in a musty smell envelops you.   The table where we sat was dirty and the bench seat had large rips.  All this can be overlooked for great food, but that was not the case. We had the corn beef sliders and they were awful.  My son had a burger and he didn’t even finish it because it wasn’t any good.  The only positive was the kind server.  We will not be going back.

This is a nice spot for a fun night out. The music is always great. Good beer. Good Scotch Eggs. Good homemade Irish food that is hardy and filling. Reminds me of the pubs I’ve been to in Ireland and England.

Best Irish food in Nashville. No doubt. It has amazing food, great service, and a unique atmosphere. Definitely one of my favorite places in the area! I would totally recommend it to anyone looking for some good eats.

restaurant.name: Monell's Restaurant
restaurant.timings: 10:30 AM to 2 PM (Mon),10:30 AM to 8:30 PM (Tue-Fri),8:30 AM to 8:30 PM (Sat),8:30 AM to 4 PM (Sun)

review.review_text: Amazing family style restaurant. Real, authentic southern cooking offering plenty of options and very filling. Definitely worth the sometimes long wait and the price. A must visit.

We had such a great experience here on New Year’s Day!  It was our first time in Nashville and we decided to check this place out based on a recommendation. We were NOT disappointed!  The food was delicious, the service was excellent, and the atmosphere was comforting!  I felt like I was at my Grandma’s house!
Absolutely love Monell's! The food, service and atmosphere is fantastic. Walk out of the restaurant with a smile on your face and a happy feeling in your soul.
The family style meal was incredible. Really hit on all the southern food I expected. Would absolutely come back on the next trip. It’s a cant miss for me

What a fun way to experience southern food and hospitality! It was like having Thanksgiving dinner early. The fried chicken, biscuits and gravy, spinach lasagna and green beans were amazing. Others at the table really enjoyed the broccoli salad and banana pudding, but I could have stopped with the top four. Service was friendly and I loved the family style dining, as I like to meet new people.

restaurant.name: Arnold's Country Kitchen
restaurant.timings: 10:30 AM to 2:45 PM (Mon-Fri),Closed (Sat-Sun)

review.review_text: If I lived in Nashville I'd come here every week! We had fried catfish, stewed okra n squash, baked chicken, mac n cheese, black beans n cornbread. Best food we've had on our trip so far!
Horrible.  The food was horrible.  Had to stand in line for over an hour, the bathrooms were out of order.  Way too pricey for the amount of food you got.  Underseasoned and gross food.

Legit 5 out of 5. Had the meatloaf, mashed potatoes, mac n cheese and last but not least green beans (the first thing gone). All were on 💥!!!! I'll be back next month when I'm here. Check it out if you haven't been.

I love, love, love southern food. What's not to love about fried chicken, corn pudding and sweet potatoes drowned in brown sugar?A big part of soul food is "Meat and three." Meat and three, which has roots in Nashville, is essentially a plate that consists of a main meat (fried chicken, meatloaf, pork chop, country ham), and three side dishes (vegetables, potatoes, macaroni and cheese).Arnold's Country Kitchen is the iconic meat-and-three restaurant. Once we parked in the Arnold's lot, we walked inside restaurant and were met with the large, open dining space. Long communal tables ran the length of the room, with few open seats spaced out in between. We added ourselves to the back of the line and waited as people filed up to the cafeteria-style counter.The menu changes a little bit by the day. And, fortunately, we were there on a meat loaf day (yum!). You can get a main and just one or two sides, but what fun is that? I wanted the full meat and three experience. So, I got the meat loaf, candied yams, macaroni and cheese, and corn pudding. I probably should've thrown something green in there, but ehhh...We just so happened to find an empty booth along the wall, so we hunkered down there before we began devouring these plates. My god, I wish this blog had tastebuds, because that meat loaf killed the game. So flavorful. So moist. So hella good. The macaroni and cheese was a delicious baked mac with some nice dark spots along the top. Sweet candied yams bathed in brown sugar were sweet as a dessert, and the corn pudding had more of a spice factor, but it was perfect for this plate of food.Just, go. Immediately. Go hungry and eat all these things. You're welcome.Grade: A

April 22, 2016 ·							by willoughbyandy ·							in Everything Else, Southeast, Tenneessee														· Leave a comment. Heading to Nashville for a day of meandering and food, we were heading to my favorite “guitar store” on the planet, Carter Vintage Guitar.  I have had Arnold’s Country Kitchen on my list for several years, since they appeared in Garden-N’-Gun’s “50 Best Southern Foods” in the fall of 2011, and was surprised to find them sharing the same parking lot.  The lunch spot was decided.

restaurant.name: Jeni's Splendid Ice Cream
restaurant.timings: 12 Noon to 11 PM (Mon-Sun)

photo.caption: ndali estate vanilla bean & yazoo sue with rosemary bar nuts

review.review_text: Pretty good in my book. It is the wife’s favorite ice cream place to date other than gelato. The variety was good. My only wish is that they had a good cookies and cream. If they did I overlooked it. Love the atmosphere and we happened to go on a beautiful day in Nashville. So it was packed and folks were eating both inside and outside. My son wore that scoop of ice cream out. So I’m sure he would give it a two thumbs up
Best ice cream spots ever! It’s so clean, delicious and the staff are wonderful at letting us try some of the flavors first. Everyone needs to come try one of their locations!
Service is fantastic, always friendly and patient! Ambiance is fun, such a great place. I absolutely loved the blackberry cobbler and churro flavors!
Delicious sweet cream and milky chocolate with a waffle cone triangle. You've gotta try it! Also really liked the strawberry. The waffle cones are made fresh here.
jeni's ice cream has unusual flavors such as Bangkok peanut ice cream that is actually spicy! Delicious waffle cones are a great bonus for sure!

restaurant.name: Taco Mamacita
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 10 PM (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Sun), 11 AM to 11 PM (Fri-Sat)

photo.caption: Enchiladas Suiza and Jalapeño Corn Slaw
Jamaican Jerk taco And Oh Voy Brisket Taco With Jalapeno/corn Slaw

review.review_text: The atmosphere and location are nice but the food has always been a little middle of the road for me. Service is generally a little slow but the margaritas are usually really good. I go if someone else suggests but its never on my list of places I'd pick. Not terrible, not great.
DELICIOUS!!!! Best taco place ever! Very friendly service. They have a lot of vegan and vegetarian options which made me very happy! Really great prices too!

Atmosphere: college and thirty something crowd, mostly locals. Decor: typical Mexican flare with a fun, eclectic, Nashville twist. Service:  as always, fantastic and attentive. Drinks:  very well crafted, correct amounts of liquor. Food: great choices, well prepared. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!!

Very good experience. Food was delivered quickly and was hot. I had the Sloppy Jose Taco and the Buffalo Chicken special, both of which were excellent. A must-visit if you are in Nashville. Couldn’t recommend more.

Well, the food was delicious, and plated well... however, IT WAS IN NO WAY GLUTEN-FREE.  Yes, they had a separate GF menu, and yes, we ordered what should have been safe.  BEWARE of cross contamination. Haven't been this sick from eating out in a long time.

restaurant.name: Puckett's Grocery & Restaurant
restaurant.timings: 7 AM to 9 PM (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Sun), 7 AM to 10 PM (Fri-Sat)

review.review_text: A staple of Franklin. Excellent Southern food, and an efficient staff. While the food is wonderful it has become a haven for tourists and should pretty much be avoided on weekends. That being said if you're fine dining at weird hours the food is well worth trying.
Hands down the best restaurant in Nashville. The food is alway good and fast.I love eating everytime I go to Nashville. Try the breakfast menu.  Ashley Kinkead

Saturday afternoon lunch. 15 minutes wait notifies by text message. Fried green tomato BLT sandwich on sourdough was excellent! Sweet potato fries were good but nothing special. Three sliders in pulled pork, chicken, and brisket were very good. Well worth the trip.

Good food. From Mississippi which has better southern food but overall was good. Wish Zomato did the .5 still. I had the chicken fried steak and it was good. Haven’t had a ton of good southernn comfy food other than this place and loveless cafe in Nashville. ✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️✔️🐳
A fun place for a date or bring the whole family. Food quality was really good. Our server was personable and attentive. Local musicians provided live music the evening we were there.

restaurant.name: Marché Artisan Foods
restaurant.timings: Closed (Mon),8 AM to 9 PM (Tue-Sat),9 AM to 4 PM (Sun)

photo.caption: Croissant French toast is light fluffy and comes with maple syrup!
Banana pudding on left with Creme brûlée  on the right

review.review_text: My favorite place for brunch in Nashville! Great drinks, great food, great atmosphere. You cannot go wrong with Marche! Just be prepared to wait in line if you go on Sunday.

We ate at so many places in Nashville in such a short amount of time, because I was really trying to touch on all of their most notable restaurants. And Nashville has no shortage of them.Marche Artisan Foods is one of those places. This European-style cafe and marketplace is located in the heart of historic East Nashville, and seemed like this perfect brunch option.The restaurant itself is very sweet with split-level dining paired up with a small marketplace. I loved the windows lining the walls of the space and the brick and exposed duct work. Just very cool.The menu for breakfast had a number of croissants, crepes, french toast, scrambled eggs and omelettes. I, however, went for a simple cheese plate which had goat cheese, peach jam and Pugliese toast. This was simple, but this was probably my favorite goat cheese I've ever had. It had just a bit of bite, but it wasn't overpowering. The jam was great, and the toast was nice and light. The perfect light option that I was just in the mood for, with the perfect ambiance and great service.Grade: A
Awesome brunch!  Had a tasty app of assorted breads and spreads and the Savory Crepes washed down with a few stout Mimosas. Great location and atmosphere.
Absolutely amazing Avocado Tartine.  A delicious piece of artisan bread topped with avocado and a mix of light greens. Highly recommend Marche as a great spot for breakfast/brunch with friends!

We had an excellent lunch.  My daughter, who is not afraid to try different foods, enjoyed her quinoa burger.  My wife's savory crepes had a perfect amount of cheese.  My salmon carpaccio disappeared completely - awesome.  The star of the lunch was the homemade orange marmalade served with the cheese plate appetizer.  We bought some of the marmalade to go.

restaurant.name: Rotier's Restaurant
restaurant.timings: 10:30 AM to 9:30 PM (Mon-Tue),10:30 AM to 10 PM (Wed-Fri),9 AM to 10 PM (Sat),Closed (Sun)

photo.caption: Rotier's Restaurant - Cheeseburger on French Bread

review.review_text: Best work lunch I’ve had so far in Nashville. So glad to eat some honest country cookin and not all this modern crap Nashville keeps popping up with. Tons of daily blue plates at a great price. Super friendly staff and awesome environment. I will be back. 4.5 rating is on point.

A good burger.  This place is considered an institution in Nashville.  I had a classic burger on a bun with everything no cheese with onion rings and a vanilla shake.  We had a long wait but the service was very fast. Burger was very good.
Very good restaurant/ bar. I had the open faced roast beef sandwich. It was just what I was looking for. I wish I was hungrier, I would have liked to try the Rueben or a burger.

We stumbled across this place looking for lunch one day and I'm glad we tried it.  It seems like an old dive and there were many people in there enjoying lunch.  We had great service too.  Apparently they are known for the french bread burger so that's what I ordered. It was good but nothing so special that I will go out of my way to go back.  We also had fries and onion rings too.  They have cold beer too! All good. Totally greased it up but sometimes you just need to!

Horrible Customer Service!!   Wish I could give this review no stars! We were told we were the next large party by one owner and the older owner (who has no customer service skills ) gave the next big table to a party that came in after us because they were a larger party. We came in 10 mins before the party that they seated. After we had waited 45 mins, they expected us to wait for a different table. We weren't able to eat with all of family and forced to leave!  Older owner pretty much blew us off because it was his mistake. We will never eat at this substandard restaurant - who cares how good their burgers are if they have horrible service!

restaurant.name: The Smiling Elephant
restaurant.timings: (Sun),Lunch, Dinner (Mon-Fri),Dinner (Sat)

photo.caption: Shrimp pad Thai. My favorite is chicken
Tom Kha Gai,wonderfully fragrant soup - Tom Kha Gai

review.review_text: The story goes like this, Sam Kopsombut who came to Nashville 30 years ago from Thailand, opened an auto repair shop. At lunch they would break and cook traditional Thai dishes for the staff. One day a customer came to pick up his car during lunch and Sam offered him lunch. This customer was so impressed with his lunch he told Sam he should be fixing lunch and dinner instead of cars.  So Sam remodeled the house above the garage and The Smiling Elephant was born and those of us who live in Nashville are very happy for the change in career.
Food and service were good. Dining room is small and you fell like you're sitting with everyone else. Not a deal breaker by any means. Would recommend and plan to return.
Good/Bad. Good food. Limited seating. Long waiting. You can touch all tables next tou you - hear all conversations.
Best Thai restaurant in Nashville, hands down.... Always great; make sure to arrive early, it's a tiny restaurant and always popular.  Pot stickers are a must.
We had a group of 6 that ate here. It was everyone's first visit and we all throughly enjoyed our meal. From the appetizers to the main entrée it was delicious. Worth a visit.

restaurant.name: Thai Phooket
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 9 PM (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Sun), 11 AM to 10 PM (Fri-Sat)

review.review_text: What a great little find in a land of BBQ! Great flavor, simple atmosphere and quick service. Always fun to find excellent Thai food where you least expect it!

This place looks a little iffy from the outside but I has a nice, clean open interior. They are very nice here, have good service and prices. The green chicken curry was great. It had excellent flavor, veggies and tender chicken. The Thai tea was also really good. The only thing that wasn't to my liking was the papaya salad, which was too salty. I'll be back next time I'm in town.

This is some of the best, if not the best Thai Food I have ever had. I have only been here once but that will change. The place is located across from Nissan Stadium. It's a modest building but the food is outstanding. The only knock I have is that wasn't as hot as I requested. I always ask for Thai hot. There was plenty of pepper sauce at the table to adjust heat levels but this was one time I actually enjoyed the flavor as it was served. Very intense and deep flavors in all three items I ordered.

Once you get past the fact that this restaurant resides in a trailer, this is one of the best Thai places you can go in Nashville.  I usually get the drunken noodle, which is a perfect mix of sweetness and spice.

Delicious food, friendly staff, efficient service. I definitely recommend it if you are in the mood for authentic, tasty Thai food. There was a constant flow of customers and not a long wait for anything. The red curry, squid salad, dumpling soup, and mango sticky rice was amazing. Even the aromas were exquisite. A+

restaurant.name: Mas Tacos Por Favor
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 4 PM (Mon-Tue),11 AM to 8 PM (Wed-Fri),10 AM to 3 PM (Sat),Closed (Sun)

review.review_text: Best tacos in Nashville. Great price, very flavorful. Simple menu that will not disappoint. Definitely try and go on a day when they have tamales. *must bring cash*
Love this place- and it’s open till 9 everyday btw. Great food, efficient service. They take cash or checks only but if you forget there’s an atm on premises.

I tried a little bit of everything at Mas Tacos. The chicken and pork Tacos were some of the best I've ever had. The beef taco was pretty good, but not as spectacular. The ingredients are obviously very fresh and the guys running the place clearly know their way around a taco. The atmosphere is fun if you're into hole-in-the-wall places, which I am. It's nothing fancy but the tacos were worth the trip from Franklin. I'd come again. Make sure you have cash to pay because they don't accept credit cards. I learned this the hard way and had to wait in line twice. Still worth it.
Best tacos I've ever had! You can't go wrong with anything on the menu. But  you're gonna have to be willing to wait in line...and make sure you've got cash on you because that's all they take.

My favorite restaurant in Nashville. We went last summer and there seemed to be just locals there. This past weekend we went and it seems all the tourists know about Mas Tacos now. The tacos are simple and fresh, and perfect. The elotes are addictive. I wish I lived in Nashville just to be close to this restaurant.

restaurant.name: Las Paletas Gourmet Popsicles
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 6 PM (Mon, Sun), 11 AM to 8 PM (Tue-Sat)

review.review_text: Gourmet Popsicles for a pretty fair price. Very fresh tasting and a pretty wide variety. I totally approve. Not much seating, but I don't know why you'd need to sit to eat a Popsicle.
Delicious. The perfect treat on a hot day. Fresh and delicious!
Average. Many of their flavors are basic and not too inventive and the popsicles are fairly small for the $3 price.
Fall in love with this man. Please help me to find this man. He really likes las Paletas.

Better than diy yogurt. We came in from memphis and my husband really wanted to go to las paletas. it is a cute place but there aren't that many places to sit which is kind of annoying. the paletas are REALLY good. i had mexican caramel and he had hot chocolate with chili. his was amazing. it was so strange to have something cold but spicy at the same time.

restaurant.name: Burger Up
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 10 PM (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Sun), 11 AM to 11 PM (Fri-Sat)

photo.caption: Beets & arugula salad, add salmon, dressing on the side - very good

review.review_text: This place is always crowded because of its tasty burger and fries, they have the best fries and comes with burger.. on weekend its difficult to find place here...Burger are tasty but they have less vegetarian option but over all location is good,service is great only issue is its little cost compare other in same location.

This place was amazing...we will definitely be back! I had The Bird and my husband had a burger and then aioli garlic parmesan fries! The homemade Ketchup and honey mustard are amazing! I forgot to take my pic but I know will be back. We also saw the Tennessee mural around the corner so a wonderful experience! We LOVE TN!!!!
A real winner. Upscale variety of all sorts of burgers. Good salads. Awesome fries of all kind, especially good sweet potato fries and truffle fries. Full bar.  Cool atmosphere.
Excellent Food! We came here after a long day of apartment hunting and it was perfect. They have generous vegetarian options for a burger restaurant and their veggie burger is awesome!!

Very trendy spot. More for socializing and drinking than getting great food. After waiting two hours, the burger was dry and boring. Onion rings and fries were just OK. Yet expensive. Overall, very unimpressed, but I went on a very busy night. Regardless, won't be going back when there are so many other options.

restaurant.name: Maggiano's Little Italy
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 10 PM (Mon-Thu), 11 AM to 11 PM (Fri), 11:30 AM to 11 PM (Sat), 11:30 AM to 9 PM (Sun)

review.review_text: Very good Italian spot! The bread is some of the best I've had at a restaurant. For my main course, I ordered the lobster Carbonara. Flavors were on point. There was bacon in it which automatically made it enjoyable. Nice texture from the snap peas. Relatively good price considering the quality of food and atmosphere. My girlfriend and I ate for $60. Make sure to book a reservation or you'll end up waiting an hour and a half like me. I wouldn't really recommend outdoor dining. The tables for 2 are pretty small and cluttered. I was kinda scared I was gonna knock something over. Overall this was a stellar experience and I definitely plan on returning (with reservations this time).

Atmosphere, food and service were all outstanding! Very romantic setting. Make a reservation ahead of time, especially on weekends! Portions are massive. My one minuscule complaint is that the restroom is down a pretty steep set of stairs. At almost 8 months pregnant it was quite inconvenient. I can only imagine what it would be like after sharing a bottle of wine.

Late night dining on a Friday night. Seated 10 minutes after resser time.  Our server Ashley was great.....friendly, knowledgable, timely.   No apps this trip as we had one prior to dining. Chopped salad was good, Gnocchi dish was rich and flavorful and my Di Mare with penne was a seafood extravaganza.   A lot of food and we also had hot bread with olive oil.  Packed some to go and would be back on another trip.  Valet parking is $3.
Wonderful meal, great server, he was very engaging. We were seated promptly (had reservations). And enjoyed a great dinner with great atmosphere.
Fantastic authentic Italian dishes. The chicken Parmesan was a huge serving. The lasagna was amazing. The split 2 deal with the option of taking an additional entree to-go is worth it!
